-- Gold Little-Changed in London After ECB Rate Cut; Silver Gains
-- B y   M a r i a   K o l e s n i k o v a
-- 2013-05-02T11:52:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-02/gold-little-changed-in-london-after-ecb-rate-cut-silver-gains.html
Gold for immediate delivery traded
little-changed in  London  after advancing as much as 0.4 percent
to $1,463.72 an ounce after the European Central Bank cut rates
to a record low.  Silver rose 0.9 percent to $23.872 an ounce.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maria Kolesnikova at 
 mkolesnikova@bloomberg.net  